registry.title: Autonomous System (AS) Numbers
registry.note: The Autonomous System (AS) numbers are used by various routing protocols. AS numbers are Assigned to the regional registries by the IANA. AFRINIC <hostmaster&afrinic.net> APNIC <helpdesk&apnic.net> ARIN <hostmaster&arin.net> LACNIC <hostmaster&lacnic.net> RIPE-NCC <ncc&ripe.net> AS Numbers can be obtained from the registry in your region. Listed below are the Assigned blocks to the regional registries.
